Snaphsot-Tree Object
File-Blob Object
Commit Object

Git DVCS (Distributed Version Control System)is a file based index system with unique key value
Commit>Snapshot>File
When we commit, if new files are added, Git adds them to the File Object, compresses them
and adds a hash to the snapshot object.
When we commit, if NO new files are added, Git compresses the File Object and
adds a hash to the snapshot object.

Three states/Git Environments
Modified      Staged (Packaging stage)         Commited Tree
Working Tree   Staging Tree-binary file        Local Repository

